- internal/index/index.go - NEW. Schema DDL consts, Open(path), Reindex(ctx, store) that builds temp+rename, typed query helpers (e.g. ListRuns, RunsWithStage) for the future-use bead. Imports modernc.org/sqlite, refstore, runmanifest, eval.
- internal/index/reindex.go (or in index.go) - the walk+insert logic.
- internal/cli/reindex.go - NEW. cobra command + runner (mirror gc.go), git-dir resolution helper.
- internal/cli/root.go - add cmd.AddCommand(newReindexCommand(...)).
- go.mod / go.sum - add modernc.org/sqlite.

**Tests:**
- internal/index: reindex from seeded temp repo (initCaptureRepo + runmanifest.Writer/eval.Writer) -> assert row counts and specific rows (a run's stages, an eval's eval_sources/targets).
- idempotent: reindex twice yields identical row counts/content.
- empty store -> schema created, zero rows.
- malformed manifest -> Reindex errors naming the ref; prior db unchanged (atomicity via temp+rename).
- internal/cli/reindex_test.go: command registered (`reindex --help`); end-to-end reindex with --db-path into temp dir asserts summary output + file exists; reindex inside repo writes to .git/etude-index.db.

**Docs:** Add docs/reindex.md (mirror docs/run.md/gc style): db location, derived/disposable, full-rebuild semantics, driver note. Update BRIEF §4 command table if it tracks status. Generated command reference (if any) regenerated separately. Note in docs/run.md that the index exists but run list does not yet consume it.

**Risks:** modernc.org/sqlite is a sizeable new dep tree (acceptable, justified). Go 1.26 compatibility of modernc must be confirmed at implement time (pin a recent version). Concurrency: single-writer full-rebuild + atomic rename avoids partial-state readers. None blocking.

